# Chapter 4: The Return


# Scene 4-1: The Tea Is Still Warm
background test_room fade

actor show Clara preset:dir_left|preset:body_coat|face=happy at 1

"" "Eve shot to her feet."

actor show Eve neutral at 2
"Eve" "You found it?{change:Eve,surprise}"

"" "Clara handed her the letter."

"Clara" "Confirm first.{change:Clara,preset:dir_left|preset:body_coat|face=happy}"

"" "Eve took the letter."
"" "Her hands were steady, but her breath caught for a beat."
"" "She didn't open it right away. Instead, she examined the creases, the seal, the edges of the paper."
"" "Then she turned it over."
"" "The outward-facing side had a name written neatly on it. The seal was held by a slightly outdated green tree sticker. The creases were old, as though it had been folded many times. It looked like something that had been flipped through carelessly, with a few wrinkles and stains."
"" "Eve's expression shifted from confusion to something more complicated."

"Eve" "This is...{change:Eve,surprise}"

"" "She looked up at Clara."

"Eve" "This letter doesn't look anything like the one described in the commission."

"Clara" "That's why we need to confirm. Of course, the simpler way is to just unfold it completely."

"" "Eve opened the letter. Her hands trembled slightly."
"" "Fully unfolded, the pages revealed dense writing. I didn't look closely, but from Eve's expression, she had already confirmed it was the stolen letter."

"" "{change:Eve,cry}Eve seemed reluctant to look at it."

"Eve" "It's the one.{change:Eve,neutral}{wait:1.0}"

"Me" "No need to double-check the contents?"

"Eve" "No. No need."

"" "Her voice had regained its composure. The kind of calm that comes after checking every last corner."

"Eve" "I also know... what I missed."

"" "Clara picked up the tea I had brewed and took a sip."

"Clara" "Just right."

"Me" "You come back from someone's windowsill and the first thing you comment on is the tea?"

"Clara" "A detective must maintain elegance."

"Me" "You have leaves stuck to your pant legs."

"" "Clara looked down, plucked off the leaves, and tossed them into the wastebasket."

"Clara" "Now I'm elegant."

"" "Eve carefully placed the letter into a file folder."

"Eve" "Where did you find it?"

"Clara" "The hanging letter rack next to the desk. Top shelf, most visible spot."

"" "Eve's face went a shade paler."

"Eve" "I checked there.{change:Eve,cry}"

"Clara" "I know."

"Eve" "I even touched every single letter in that rack."

"Me" "So she used your own methods against you."

"Me" "You were too certain the letter couldn't be hidden inside another letter. Because you knew the thickness was wrong, the seal was wrong, the edges were wrong."

"Clara" "And that letter hadn't gotten thicker, hadn't been slipped into a false layer, and had no extra seal."

"Eve" "Because it was the letter itself."

"Clara" "Right. She flipped the letter over, flattened it repeatedly along the old creases in reverse, wrote a new address on the outside, and sealed it with a new sticker. That way, it just looked like an ordinary piece of mail casually left in the letter rack.{change:Clara,preset:body_coat|face=happy}"

"Me" "So ordinary, so worn, so conspicuous that it was even easier to dismiss as irrelevant."

"Eve" "In plain sight.{change:Eve,neutral}"

"Clara" "In plain sight."

# Scene 4-2: Confirming the Disguise
scene_break test_room fade

play bgm circulation

actor show Eve neutral at 2
"" "Eve stared at the file folder, as if reexamining every search she had conducted over the past month."

"Eve" "If Clara hadn't told me about this disguise technique—even if I went back and checked the letter rack again, I might still have missed it.{change:Eve,cry}"

"Me" "Because you wouldn't check the contents of each letter."

"Eve" "No. For one thing, it would be too much of an invasion of privacy. And for me, as long as the recipient didn't match, the thickness was normal, and there was no hidden compartment—it couldn't be the target."
actor show Clara face=neutral at 1
"Clara" "That was her entire strategy."

"" "Clara set down her teacup."

"Clara" "She didn't need to hide the letter. She just needed to make it 'not exist' by your definition."

"" "Eve responded with silence."

"Clara" "Eve, you didn't lose to her hiding skills."

"Eve" "Then what did I lose to?"

"Clara" "Your own standards. They were too precise, and that precision left blind spots.{change:Clara,preset:body_coat|face=happy}"

"" "Eve laughed softly—this time not from embarrassment or nerves."

"Eve" "Thank you.{change:Eve,smile}"

"" "She looked at Clara, then at me."

"Eve" "Thank you both.{change:Eve,smile}"

# Scene 4-3: The Switch
scene_break test_room fade

"Me" "Wait a second."

actor show Clara face=neutral at 1
"Clara" "What?"

"Me" "You just took the letter?"

"Clara" "Of course not."

"Me" "Then what did you do?"

"" "Clara pulled out her phone from her pocket and showed the first photo in her gallery."
"" "In it was a letter sitting on the letter rack—no, a letter that looked almost identical to the one from before."

"Clara" "I left a replacement.{change:Clara,preset:dir_left|face=happy}"

actor show Eve surprise at 2
"Eve" "A replacement?{change:Eve,neutral}"

"Clara" "About the same size and appearance, folded similarly. She won't notice unless she opens it."

"Me" "What if she does open it?"

"Clara" "Then she'll see some writing."

"Me" "What did you write?"

"" "{change:Clara,preset:dir_left|face=serious}Clara averted her eyes."

"Me" "Clara."

"Clara" "Nothing much."

"Me" "What did you write?"

"Clara" "{change:Clara,preset:dir_left|face=neutral}Just something perfectly ordinary, like 'left in too obvious a spot, spotted it right away.'"

"Eve" "Hmm..."

"Clara" "Ah, of course I didn't mean anything bad about Eve."

"Eve" "It's fine, I don't mind.{change:Eve,neutral}"

"Clara" "{change:Clara,preset:dir_left|face=happy}And then I wrote that the window wasn't locked properly."
play bgm waiting

"Me" "That's just taunting her! Besides, even if the window were locked, it wouldn't stop you, would it?{speed:45}"

"Clara" "But the window really wasn't locked properly."

"Eve" "So what you're saying is, you left a taunting letter in her room."

"Clara" "It's a detective's calling card."

"Me" "Please don't give detectives a bad name."

"Clara" "Relax, I didn't sign it."

"Me" "That's not the issue!"

"" "Eve pressed her fingers to her temple."

"Eve" "I'll handle it.{change:Eve,neutral}"

"Me" "You're already sounding like a victim."

"Eve" "Perhaps."

"Clara" "But this way, it'll take her longer to realize the letter's been taken. At least before she actually tries to use her leverage, she won't realize she's only holding an empty shell.{change:Clara,preset:body_coat|face=happy}"
play bgm circulation

"Me" "That reasoning actually holds up."

"Clara" "My reasoning always holds up."

"Me" "Not when you came in through the window."

