"" "Eve thought for a moment."

"Eve" "I don't know. But that's not my decision to make.{change:Eve,neutral}"

"Eve" "What I can do is make sure she's no longer threatened by this letter. The rest is her own fight."

"" "Clara nodded. She didn't ask further."
"" "Neither did I."
"" "Not because we weren't curious. But because—Eve had spent two weeks on this. If she chose to trust the letter owner's judgment, then we had no reason not to trust Eve's."

"Me" "Then our commission is complete."

"Eve" "Mm."

"" "She looked toward the door."
"" "I didn't know if we'd meet again after she walked through that door..."
"" "But then again, would meeting again be better, or would not meeting be better? I couldn't really say."

